11/05/2010
ROME, Italy -- Police arrested dozens of suspected mobsters on Monday (May 10th) and seized a large stash of weapons, most of which allegedly came from Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). During raids at several locations in southern Italy, police found rocket and grenade launchers, automatic weapons and grenades. BiH Deputy Foreign Minister Ana Trisic-Babic said that Bosnian authorities will contact Italy about launching an investigation into the weapons' smuggling. (RTRS, Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine, AP, Reuters - 10/05/10)
